HEADWORD: Brother german
<hw>Broth"er ger"man</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A
brother by both the father's and mother's side, in contradistinction to
a <contr>uterine brother</contr>, one by the mother only.</def>
<rj><au>Bouvier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Brotherhood</ent>⟦br⟧
